The '''NYU Veterans Writing Workshop''' at [[New York University]] in [[Manhattan]], [[New York (state)|New York]] is a free, non-partisan outreach program offered to the veteran community in and around [[New York City]]<ref name=about>{{cite web |url= http://www.nyuvetsworkshop.org/ |title=About The Workshop |last= |first= |date= |website=NYU Veterans Writing Workshop |publisher=New York University |access-date=23 November 2016 |quote=}}</ref> and is considered by some as the pre-eminent writing workshop for veterans.<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://atwar.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/09/09/how-to-run-a-successful-writing-workshop-for-veterans/?_r=0| title=How to Run a Successful Writing Workshop for Veterans |author=Matt Gallagher | date=September 9, 2013| work=The New York Times}}</ref>
== History == {{expand section|date=January 2015}} The workshop began in 2008,<ref name="haberman">{{Cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/11/24/nyregion/24nyc.html?_r=0| title=Moving the Battlefield to the Page |author=Clyde Haberman | date=November 23, 2009| work=The New York Times}}</ref> founded by former [[United States Ambassador to Ireland]] [[Jean Kennedy Smith]].<ref name=about />
== Alumni == Notable alumni of the workshop include:
{{Div col|colwidth=30em}} *[[Jason Everman]] <ref>{{cite press release |last=O’Sullivan |first= Anna |date= May 7, 2013 |title= Former Nirvana Guitarist, U.S. Army Veteran, Monk to Graduate Columbia University |url= https://gs.columbia.edu/news-press?article=former-nirvana-guitarist-us-army-veteran-monk-graduates-columbia-university |location=New York |publisher=Columbia University’s School of General Studies |agency= |access-date=2016-11-23}}</ref> *[[Phil Klay]]<ref name="haberman" /> *[[Matt Gallagher]]<ref name=Moreau>{{Cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/1986/05/25/magazine/can-writing-be-taught-in-iowa.html | title=Veterans’ Reading at NYU |author=Craig Moreau | date=May 3, 2012| work=Electric Literature}}</ref> *[[Roy Scranton]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kennedy-center.org/artist/B85913 |title=The NYU Veterans Writing Workshop |last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher=The Kennedy Center |access-date=23 November 2016 |quote=}}</ref> {{div col end}}
